<br>
Unfortunately, it has been my experience that the average group tank simply does not understand yet how crucial it is to help the group Mage out with positioning. Many tanks I have grouped with simply believe this to be the backstabber's problem to work out.<br>
<br>
While its true for a PC rogue or monk that they can quite easily strafe around to a mob's back, the same is not true for a pet owner. I must laboriously walk my pet around to the mob's back after backing it off, then re-engage. Every time the mob moves, I must repeat the process.<br>
<br>
First of all, when the pet is backed off the group loses what is probably 100 dps, whereas a traditional rogue or monk can strafe around while attacking. It's not a lot at any time, a few seconds here and there, but if it takes me 3 seconds to get the pet in place and it happens 4 times per fight, that's a nuke worth of damage.<br>
<br>
Secondly, while I am walking the pet around, I am not meditating. Every tick I lose credit for medding costs me mana for making things burn. This also adds up, reducing group damage output and lowering the group's kill rate.<br>
<br>
Thirdly, pets not being on the back of mobs in the Planes is a very bad thing. If I just give up and make an Air pet, which reduces the impact of uncontrolled mob placement (without eliminating it mind you) I must very carefully watch for enrage. If I miss it, a quadding pet can die in seconds, often before the pet hit point bar updates.<br>
<br>
All of these problems can be cured by working with your group's pet owner to keep the pet consistently on the back. Work out where most pulls are coming from, and place the pet in the path - it won't agro random mobs wandereing past so is safe to leave it out a little from camp. This way when you turn to face the mob the pet will start out behind it.<br>
<br>
During the fight, strafe around to keep the pet on the back, its not hard to do especially when you are holding agro. Good positioning is something that a quality MT does without thinking, but unfortunately few tanks I have met really understand how to work with pets, but those that do I make a point of thanking for making the effort - it is genuinely appreciated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmlokk>Grimmlokk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 992<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/02 4:03:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2557.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets, Positioning, and PoP.</span><hr size=1>  You left off the big one.<br>
<br>
 ENRAGE!<br>
<br>
 Always always always turn mobs back to pets before enrage. And petholes, if more than 1 of you are in the group coordinate where yer pets are attacking from so they're all on the same side.<br>
<br>
 And fingertwiddlers, remember that the tank is not the only person that has to work on positioning. Can't have tank in front and 3 pets and a monk in back. Mob will move all over. If I hafta choose between a pet backstabbing or a real rogue, that mage is making an different pet to help me counterbalance the rogue. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6122"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/bustedteef2.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=h0gfather>H0gfather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/02 4:11:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2557.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.aus-1.au.nu/images/photo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets, Positioning, and PoP.</span><hr size=1> I did?<br>
